data.description: Lovely 3 bed, 2 bath home built in 2016, situated on approx. 2.61 acres, along side a mountain water, creek bed with a small peaceful waterfall. Sit on the back deck and enjoy the sound of rippling water and the smell of frest air.  It is mostly level land, with mountain views, mature blueberry bushes, a cherry tree, muscadine vines, concord and red grape vines, Japanese quince, gardenia, azaleas, wild raspberries...what more could you ask for in such a tranquil setting only a mile from Table Rock State Park!  During their ownership the sellers installed LVP flooring throughout the home, upgraded the shower head, installed a new railing on the front porch, painted/stained the deck, and paved the driveway (concrete). Several out buildings are on the property, including a storage building with loft, an old smokehouse and an additional shed. It also has an Artesian well . In the past there was a mh in the clearing to the right of the house. The crawl space is encapsulated and it also has a dehumidifier. The home is VA Handicapped compliant with wide doors, wide hallway, pocket doors for accessibility,  roll in shower and roll up sink in master. The whole home is wheelchair accessible with more than one ramp. Look no further, book your appointment today!
